      <h2 id='ops-intern'>Operations Intern</h2>
      <h3>About Westward \\ Leaning</h3>
      <p>Westward Leaning is an eyewear start-up located in the Mission District in San Francisco, founded in 2011. Our sunglasses have become popular with an early adopter audience for their <a href='/pages/the-concept'>universally flattering designs</a> and <a href='/pages/our-story'>the story behind them</a>: Each model is crafted in <a href='/pages/behind-the-scenes'>our San Francisco studio</a> in honor of a moment, a person or a place that has brought social progress in the world. Each model contains a unique material (from <a href='/products/children-of-california-1-1-redwood-wayfarer'>redwood</a> to <a href='/products/mercury-seven-stealth-3s-onyx-wayfarer'>onyx</a> to <a href='/products/louisiana-purchase-2-3-green-mirror-wayfarer'>brass</a>) representative of that story. And for each pair sold we donate a substantial amount to education-related charities.</p>
      <h3>About the role</h3>
      <p>You will report directly to the operations team and be given first-hand experience working on projects in business and operations. In addition, you will have the opportunity to see how consumer products &mdash; such as high-end fashion sunglasses &mdash; are manufactured, distributed and sold throughout the world.  We expect that the student will have an interest in working on strategic and tactical projects that will have a positive impact on our company.</p>
      <p>Responsibilities are:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Assist with fulfillment of sales orders for our website sales.</li>
        <li>Maintain accurate records of inventory levels.</li>
        <li>Collect, organize and analyze inventory and sales data.</li>
        <li>Research and study other fashion and consumer product companies including competitors.</li>
        <li>Maintain our quality standards during inspection, cleaning, and packaging of our product.</li>
        <li>Prepare and deliver a presentation on a special project at end of internship.</li>
        <li>Complete all tasks on time.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Accountabilities</h3>
      <p>By the end of your internship, you will have learned about how fashion start-ups run, and contributed to the operational success of the company. Your performance will be measured on accuracy, timeliness, and attitude. You will report directly to the Operations Manager, who will be guiding you throughout the duration of the internship.</p>
      <h3>Job Specifications</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Must be currently enrolled in an educational program.</li>
        <li>Must have strong computer literacy and telephone skills.</li>
        <li>Must be fluent in English.</li>
        <li>Must have the means to arrive at work on time on a daily basis.</li>
        <li>Must be able to package inventory (you must be detail oriented and physically able to lift a box that is 15 lbs).</li>
        <li>Must be able to focus on tasks in an open layout office setting.</li>
        <li>Must be comfortable with Microsoft Excel, basic math, and book-keeping.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Compensation</h3>
      <p>You will be compensated in accordance with federal, state and local laws and regulations.</p>
